<center>'''Level 587''', more known as "The Great Sandcastle of the Nile," is the 588th level of [[Backrooms Wiki|the Backrooms]]. It was discovered on March 17th, 2004.</center>

<div style="font-family:Montserrat Alternates; background: #f5ce4270; color: white; border: 15px double #ffffff; box-shadow: 0 0 100px #000000 inset; padding: 1rem; margin:1em; text-shadow: 0 0 10px white, 0 0 10px black; font-size: 16.5px">
<div style="font-family:Montserrat Alternates; border:3px solid #f5ce42; box-shadow: 0px 0px 7px white; padding:5px 10px; margin:1em;"><font size="6"><center>Description</center></font></div>
{{Blurimage|align=right|file=Level 587.jpg|caption=A miniature recreation of the sandcastle, found near the ocean. (2009)|width=250px}}
'''Level 587''' resembles an expansive desert with small hills and cacti scattered around. '''Level 587''' is known for its various landmarks, like the sandcastle, its ocean, or the river that flows through it. The level presents some anomalies, such as finding metal boxes periodically while wandering; these generally contain Achrophiline.

As a notable point, in the center of the entire level, there is a colossal sandcastle with a diameter of 60 miles and a length of 90 miles. This sandcastle has many rooms with different functions, such as the throne room, eateries, carpet rooms, etc. All of the sandcastle's rooms seem to follow an order or are divided between floors, which take specific roles. Food-related floors will have eateries and wine production rooms, for instance. All rooms within a floor are connected by one hallway, extending from one side of the castle to another. Everything in the sandcastle appears to be strangely arranged, every sign is obvious in what it says, every decoration is aligned, and every object is put in its correct place. 

A tall wall surrounds the sandcastle; it features a two-meter-tall gate, which is opened by a lever within the throne room. On the sandcastle side of the wall, an artificial lake between the walls and the sandcastle acts as a last safety measure. The sandcastle appears to be very resistant to rainwater. It appears to tighten the sandcastle up. However, flood and lake water will tear it apart. It is theorized that rainwater at this level contains some sort of glue that sticks the sandcastle together.

{{Blurimage|align=left|file=Level 587 2.png|caption=What is believed to be the sandcastle, seen from afar. (2004)}}

The sandcastle is heavily protected by various safety measures; for example, the walls contain a rainwater mechanism that activates when anything heavy is holding onto it. Booby traps are the most known of the safety measures, the long path to the sandcastle retains hidden darts, pits, etc. One of the most infamous of these safety measures is known as the "Sand Blinder", a swift and efficient motion-based contraption activated if other measures fail. The Sand Blinder repeatedly launches sand into a target's eyes, increasing the sand amount each launch. The mechanism will only stop once the threat is deemed incapacitated. Wanderers speak of hours of endless sand torture, blinding them, piles of sand and corpses, and the cruel creator of the Sand Blinder.

The throne room is a large room with several shelves and closets, filled with riches, trophies, and other luxurious items. The throne room has six large pillars within it, representing Level 587's main features. The throne appears to be made of spruce wood and luxurious metals, such as gold and silver. A red, orange, and yellow cloth, assumably made of wool, can be seen placed on the wall, alongside trophies, for unknown reasons. Secret compartments exist inside the walls, with the most powerful objects found, such as [[Object 13|Luck Clovers]], [[Object 14|Paperstones]], and other objects..

Lakes are encountered broadly around '''Level 587'''; around these lakes are cacti and other forms of plant life, such as Venus flytraps, and many others. Harmful fish, such as piranhas and pufferfish, may inhabit some lakes if the required food is present. Small boats may be present, floating on the lakes. Said boats will likely have chests where objects essential for survival are kept. These boats seem to perpetually float; even if retaining large holes and cracks, they do not sink. This may be due to the large amount of salt present within the lakes at this level. This amount of salt also turns the lakes to be an unreliable habitat for [[Hydrolitis Plague|Hydrolitis]], and entities in general.

{{Blurimage|align=left|file=Sand Souls.jpg|caption=A picture of a group of Sand Souls. (2005)}}

Within the confines of '''Level 587''' is an intriguing object, known as "Sand Souls". They are most naturally found on this level, but may rarely be found on other desert levels. Sand Souls appear as sand objects that occasionally alter physical states and forms. Travelers say that a faded glow may emerge from these objects from time to time. Sand Souls may be uncovered buried underground, inside corpses, and within crates in the Neo-Nile. Sand Souls appear to be a life force for all entities in '''Level 587''', it gives them strength and energy. If one were to remove a Sand Soul from an entity, it would die. Sand Souls are often used all around [[Backrooms Wiki|the Backrooms]] as fuel and for storage. Each instance of these objects can hold 5-8 liters within them before tearing apart. These are also highly volatile and must be handled with care; a wrong move could cause one to explode. If exposed to heat, a Sand Soul will rapidly catch fire, which will spread quickly. After some time, the Sand Soul may explode. However, the explosion is fairly small and causes minor injuries; first-degree burns and bruises are the most common injuries.

Within '''Level 587''', there are various environmental hazards; the most common hazards are sandstorms and floods. Environmental hazards appear to be stronger in this level. Floods are much larger and can last continuously for decades. The sandstorms are much quicker and stronger, as the sand of the sandstorms may reach 380 mph. The sand may catch onto the sandcastle, thickening its walls.

{{Blurimage|align=right|file=SandstormCastle.jpg|caption=An image of a sandstorm. Photographer alive. (2015)}}

Beside the sandcastle is a replica of the Nile River. However, this replica appears to originate from the ancient Egyptian era; it is commonly known as the "Neo-Nile". Many papyrus plants shroud the Neo-Nile, and other plants similar to it can be sighted as well. Large boats are rarely seen on the Neo-Nile, completely deserted. These boats may sometimes carry secret rooms, with crates within. If the boat breaks, the crates will likely leap out and float alone around the Neo-Nile. Rain is especially common around the Neo-Nile; the rain occurs every few days or weeks. This has triggered many floods in the area, resulting in a large quantity of damage to the sandcastle, as it is very close to the Neo-Nile.

If one strolls off far enough in '''Level 587''', they will likely be met with an enormous ocean that surrounds the desert. Travelers describe a calm ocean, with crystalline waters, thriving corals, and beautiful fauna. The ocean seems to be completely different from the Neo-Nile and other bodies of water within '''Level 587'''. The amount of salt is much lower, for instance. Strangely, no environmental hazards have been recorded in areas near the ocean. It appears to have calming properties, that cause any stressed explorers to calm down in no time.

As of the current year, the sandcastle's history remains relatively obscure. Only fragments of its history, like "wars" and dark periods, are known. However, it is widely believed that the sandcastle was built by ancient sand-like entities. It is unknown how these entities could construct such a gargantuan structure. Researchers believe it could be from Sand Souls, ancient methods, or simply time and effort.

Rumors speak of a "Sand King", a remote entity that inhabits the sandcastle, as a supposed leader of the Sand Guards, who defend the castle. The amount of safety measures drives locals to consider this Sand King a paranoid and recluse entity. It may not enjoy the presence of humans and entities alike. Investigators have been working to locate this King. A popular manner of doing so is murdering Sand Guards and reading the symbols on their bodies. Only three of these runes are translated, each meaning "act", "rock", and "mono". However, these researchers affirm that a specific rune could mean "king" or "ruler", although it is still unknown.

<div style="font-family:Montserrat Alternates; border:3px solid #f5ce42; box-shadow: 0px 0px 7px white; padding:5px 10px; margin:1em;"><font size="6"><center>Entities</center></font></div>
[[Entity 72|Foams]], [[Entity 6|Dullers]], [[Entity 4|Death Moths]], [[Entity 23|Carbonations]], [[Entity 35|Spines]] and [[Entity 190|Plastic Worms]] inhabit '''Level 587'''. [[Hydrolitis Plague|Hydrolitis]] is theorized to inhabit the Neo-Nile and the surrounding sea. Another entity commonly sighted in '''Level 587''' are the Sand Guards.

== Sand Guards ==
{{Entity Class|Agg=5|Int=2|Dan=5|Hab=Rare; Level 587|no=UND.|noname=0}}Sand Guards are rare entities who inhabit '''Level 587'''; they appear to randomly defend any piece of land that stands out in the landscape. Sand Guards are often described as robust entities, with large arms with sharp claws. Their torsos are described to additionally take on the role of the head, so their "faces" are situated on their torsos. Sand Guards do not have a conventional face, rather, they retain one large glowing eye. They use this eye to identify objects and simple patterns. Sand Guards are not very intelligent, their intelligence appears to lower as their strength grows. If a Sand Guard encounters a threat, it will chase and crush the being to death. Strange, not yet translated symbols are spread around the upper part of their bodies. These symbols appear to vary in completely unexpected manners, sometimes, a symbol may be shaped like a tragic event in [[the Frontrooms]], or a group logo or flag. Although some Sand Guards may have one or a group of symbols in common.

<div style="font-family:Montserrat Alternates; border:3px solid #f5ce42; box-shadow: 0px 0px 7px white; padding:5px 10px; margin:1em;"><font size="6"><center>Colonies & Outposts</center></font></div>
As of the current year, an estimate of three outposts exist within '''Level 587'''.

=== The Vault ===
The Vault is located on the sandcastle's lowermost, underground floor. The outpost is titularly named after the floor. The Vault, as an outpost was formed in 2010 when a group of explorers broke into the sandcastle and locked themselves in the vault of the castle. Sand Guards are always observing their every move, and guard the entrance of the Vault. Due to this, the Vault's members live off only what is already within the room, whatever food, medicine, or riches they can find. While they attempted to break out of the sandcastle, they failed every time, and the Sand Guards took notice. Since then, the Vault has never tried to escape and will die inside that room once the food ends.

=== Sandia ([[Backroom Colonists]]) ===
Sandia is a major outpost within '''Level 587'''. It is located underground, in an intricate burrow, where each member has their space. Sandia is mostly abandoned, as the signal with the [[Backroom Colonists|Backrooms Colonists]] had been cut. The residents of Sandia usually leave to hunt Plastic Worms or collect algae and Sand Souls. Sandia frequently uses buried Sand Souls as fire during nighttime, or as storage. During darkness, it is common for inhabitants to dig holes to hide their possessions, which were previously stored in Sand Souls. This is done to use the Soul as a campfire, however, some Souls are left to be utilized later, rather than burnt.<div style="font-family:Montserrat Alternates; border:3px solid #f5ce42; box-shadow: 0px 0px 7px white; padding:5px 10px; margin:1em;"><font size="6"><center>Entrances & Exits</center></font></div>
== Entrances ==

* Entering a castle-shaped structure in [[Level 46]].
* One of the islands on [[Level 149]] may take one here.
* A sign may indicate where the wanderer can go to reach '''Level 587''' in [[Level 91]].
* [[Level 200]] contains entrances to '''Level 587'''. Although, most are unknown.
* Breaking into the walls of the cave in [[Level 323]].
* Wanderers report that lights on [[Level 401]] will deform before being teleported here.

== Exits ==

* Periodically, sandstone structures may manifest within the desert, entering then will take one to [[Level 46]].
* No-clipping through the plants of a garden will lead to [[Level 214]].
* Being blinded by the sand has a small chance to lead to [[Level 174]].
* Suffocating on the sand will take one to [[Level 671]].
* An orange chair may manifest on the sandcastle, staying nearby for too long will lead to [[Level 91]].
* In the path to the castle, if one goes back, they may enter [[Level 157]].
*</div>
